<HEADLINE> Dow Loses 111; Nasdaq Sheds 75  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell sharply Thursday as investors'
enthusiasm disappeared following the Federal Reserve's announcement
on interest rates.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was down 111.41 at 10,416.42.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators also dropped. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index was down 13.99 at 1,440.83, and the Nasdaq composite index
was down 74.85 at 3,865.49.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, the Fed left interest rates unchanged, but noted
that inflation risks remain in the economy. The warning on
inflation led many analysts to expect that the Fed will raise rates
at its August meeting.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't think the game is over. This is more like the seventh
inning stretch,'' said John Forelli, senior vice president at
Independence Investment Associates in Boston. ''The Fed is waiting
to see whether economic activity slows substantially. I don't think
any investors can rule out action in August.''
</P>
<P>
   In the meantime, analysts said, the market may find excuses to
remain stalled in a narrow range. Stocks had advanced modestly in
the days leading up to the meeting, leading investors to take some
profits Thursday. Also, traders said investors were unloading some
stocks ahead of the Fourth of July weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Financial stocks, which are highly sensitive to rising interest
rates, pulled the Dow lower. J.P. Morgan fell $2.063 to $114.563
and American Express fell 75 cents to $52.438.
</P>
<P>
   But investors were also taking profits from the technology
stocks that have risen in recent sessions. LSI Logic fell $5.75 to
$53.25 and Cisco fell $2.375 to $61.188.
</P>
<P>
   On the New York Stock Exchange, Eli Lilly soared $13.125 to
$100.25 after announcing that an independent board gave a favorable
review to its drug Zovant, used to treat sepsis. The experimental
drug, if approved, would be the first drug approved for the
treatment of sepsis, a disease in which the body's systems fail due
to infection.
</P>
<P>
   Unisys plunged $8.25 to $15.375 lowered guidance on its
second-quarter revenue and earnings. Investors are enacting fierce
penalties on companies that demonstrate any evidence of earnings
weakness.
</P>
<P>
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7-to-5 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 458.39 million
shares, slightly ahead of Wednesday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 8.10 to 512.89.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
