<HEADLINE> Meg Ryan, Dennis Quaid Separating  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Meg Ryan and Dennis Quaid have announced they
are separating after nearly 10 years of marriage.
</P>
<P>
   Their publicist, Lisa Kasteler, declined to say whether the two
plan to divorce. She said the separation began about six weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   ''The couple hope that the press will respect their privacy
during this difficult time,'' Kasteler said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan, 38, who began filming the kidnap thriller ''Proof of
Life'' in May, endeared herself to American movie audiences with
such romantic comedies as ''When Harry Met Sally,'' ''Sleepless in
Seattle,'' and ''You've Got Mail.''
</P>
<P>
   Quaid, 46, starred in the sci-fi time traveling tale
''Frequency'' in May and is known for roles in ''Breaking Away,''
''The Big Easy'' and ''Wyatt Earp.''
</P>
<P>
   The two met in 1987 on the set of ''Innerspace.'' They married
in 1991 and have an 8-year-old son. They also appeared together in
''Flesh and Bone'' in 1993.
