<HEADLINE> Met Hamilton's Rehab on Hold  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORT ST. LUCIE, Fla. (AP) -- New York Mets outfielder Darryl
Hamilton, sidelined by a toe injury, has left the team's St. Lucie
farm club to see a doctor in California.
</P>
<P>
   Hamilton, out since the first week of the season, played his
first minor league rehab game Wednesday, going 1-for-3 as the
designated hitter in St. Lucie's 10-8 loss to Daytona.
</P>
<P>
   ''We want to make sure everything is fine with it until we take
it to the next level,'' Hamilton said. ''They want me to see the
doctor who performed the surgery. He'll make the decision as to
whether it's OK or not and we'll go from there.''
</P>
<P>
   Hamilton was lifted for a pinch hitter when he was slated to
come to the plate for his fourth at-bat Wednesday. St. Lucie
manager Dave Engle said Hamilton was replaced because he needed to
pick up a new prescription from a pharmacy.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm not on a timetable,'' Hamilton said. ''I'm kind of taking
it easy and making sure everything is fine because I don't want to
come back too soon to where I'd have to go on the DL again.''
</P>
<P>
   Hamilton split last season with Colorado and New York, hitting
.339 in 55 games for the Mets.
</P>
