<HEADLINE> Keeneland Introduces Online Package  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Keeneland is taking its horse sales online
in an effort to attract more buyers.
</P>
<P>
   The system will start with an online entry process for the
November Breeding Stock Sale. The announcement was made Thursday to
inform consignors of the new option. Entries close Aug. 1.
</P>
<P>
   ''This new online entry process will help all consignors from
the largest to the smallest,'' said Rogers Beasley, Keeneland's
Director of Sales.
</P>
<P>
   The online system can be accessed at Keeneland's home page,
http://www.keeneland.com, beginning in mid-July. The existing entry
system also will still be available to consignors.
</P>
<P>
   The next addition to the system will be an online Reserve Not
Attained sale to be held in conjunction with the September Yearling
Sale.
</P>
<P>
   Other features of the new interactive auction system include the
capability for the online sale of yearlings, broodmares, foals,
horses in training, stallion shares and seasons, credit checks,
authorization of agents and settlement of accounts, and updated
catalog information availability.
</P>
