<HEADLINE> Capitals Agree With Billington  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Craig Billington agreed to terms on a
three-year contract Thursday with the Washington Capitals.
</P>
<P>
   The deal will pay the 33-year-old goalie $787,500 next season,
$827,000 in 2001-2002 and $868,000 in the final year.
</P>
<P>
   Billington recently finished his first season with Washington in
which he appeared in 13 games. He was 3-6-1 with a 2.75 GAA and
.910 save percentage.
</P>
<P>
   Combined with No. 1 goalie Olaf Kolzig, the Washington duo had
the fourth lowest team GAA (2.33) in the NHL last season.
</P>
<P>
   Billington was acquired by the Capitals from Colorado on July
16, for future considerations. He has also played for New Jersey,
Ottawa and Boston in a 12-year career.
</P>
