<HEADLINE> Ecuador 2, Peru 1  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Klever Chala and Eduardo Hurtado each scored to push
Ecuador
past Peru 2-1 Thursday in a qualifying game for the 2002 World Cup.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Chala initiated the scoring in the 14th minute with a
shoulder-high shot on a ball softly passed by Hurtado with his
head.
</P>
<P>
   Hurtado scored the second goal in the 50th minute, taking
advantage of a bouncing free kick in front of the Peruvian net.
</P>
<P>
   After a listless first half in Quito, Peru came back to score
its lone goal in the 74th minute on a free kick by Nolberto Solano
that Juan Pajuelo nudged past goalie Jose Cevallos with his head.
</P>
<P>
   Ecuador dominated the first half, demonstrating an orderly
offense, keeping the play in front of Peru's net. However, Ecuador
forward Agustin Delgado missed two clear opportunities to score.
</P>
<P>
   Peru came back in the second half after Ecuador coach Hernan
Dario Gomez pulled midfielder Alex Aguinaga and forwards Hurtado
and Agustin Delgado in the 70th minute.
</P>
<P>
   But Ecuador hung on to win.
</P>
</TEXT>
