<HEADLINE> D-Backs' Durazo Placed on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- First baseman Erubiel Durazo on Thursday became
the third member of the Arizona Diamondbacks to be placed on the
disabled list this week.
</P>
<P>
   Durazo, who had surgery on his right wrist to repair cartilage
damage June 1, was placed on the 15-day disabled list before
Thursday night's game against the Houston Astros.
</P>
<P>
   Durazo joins third baseman Matt Williams and right-hander Todd
Stottlemyre on the 15-day disabled list. Like Williams, sidelined
with a right quadriceps strain, Durazo is expected to return after
the All-Star break. Stottlemyre isn't expected to return until
September because of tendinitis in his right elbow.
</P>
<P>
   Durazo played two games since he was activated June 24, hitting
a three-run homer during the Diamondbacks' 8-3 victory over
Colorado on Sunday. Durazo is hitting .276 with seven homers and 27
RBIs in 47 games.
</P>
<P>
   Arizona manager Buck Showalter said Durazo will begin his
rehabilitation assignment on July 4 in Tucson while the
Diamondbacks travel to Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Durazo was replaced on the 25-man roster by outfielder Jason
Conti, who hit .308 in 78 games for Triple-A Tucson.
</P>
</TEXT>
