<HEADLINE> Show Falcon Wins After Jockey Spill  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Show Falcon won the $62,900 feature race
at Churchill Downs by disqualification Thursday following a mishap
near the finish that injured jockey Tony D'Amico.
</P>
<P>
   D'Amico's mount, Claire's Honor, became entangled in the legs of
Ican'thearyou and went to his knees as those horses and Show Falcon
battled for the lead in the 1 1/16-mile race. D'Amico was thrown to
the turf and struck by the hoof of a trailing horse.
</P>
<P>
   D'Amico was motionless on the track for several minutes, and the
track's attending physician, Dr. Robert Crouch, said D'Amico was
briefly unconscious. After he regained consciousness, D'Amico was
transported to the emergency room at University of Louisville
hospital.
</P>
<P>
   D'Amico was ''awake and alert'' and suffering from some back and
shoulder pain later, Crouch said. Ican'thearyou crossed the finish
line a neck in front of Show Falcon, but stewards disqualified the
apparent winner for failing to maintain a straight course.
Ican'thearyou was placed last in the six-horse field.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier, jockey Pat Day won the seventh race aboard Alpine at
Clark to move within three victories of 2,000 for his career at
Churchill Downs. Day has eight scheduled mounts on Friday's card.
</P>
</TEXT>
