<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 21:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Toy Cars in Cereal Boxes Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Kellogg Co. is recalling 837,000 toy cars
packaged in cereal boxes because the tires can detach from the car
wheels, posing a choking hazard.
</P>
<P>
   The Battle Creek, Mich., company received two reports of the
tires detaching from the car wheels, but no injuries have been
reported, the Consumer Product Safety Commission said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The NASCAR Pull'N Go Hot Wheels cars are red and yellow with a
white hood. ''Kellogg's'' is written on the hood, and the number
''5'' and ''Terry Labonte'' is written on the roof. The words
''China'' and ''MFG. FOR KELLOGG CO. TM'' is printed on the
underside. Pulling the car backward a few inches on a surface
causes it to roll forward.
</P>
<P>
   Several grocery stores nationwide sold the cars in specially
marked boxes of Kellogg's Tri-Fun-Pak 40-ounce box, Kellogg's Froot
Loops 43.6-ounce box, Kellogg's Mini-Wheats Frosted Bite Size
58.8-ounce box and Kellogg's Crispix 31.4-ounce box. The cars were
distributed inside the boxes from March to June of this year.
</P>
<P>
   Consumers are advised to take the toy cars away from young
children immediately, and send the cars to Kellogg to get a free
replacement item and postage reimbursement. The car can be sent to
Kellogg Company, P.O. Box 185654, Battle Creek, MI 49018-5654. For
more information, consumers can call Kellogg at 1-800-962-0037 or
check its Web site at www.kelloggs.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
