<HEADLINE> Woman, Kids Killed in Puerto Rico  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   UTUADO, Puerto Rico (AP) -- A woman and her four children were
found decapitated in their house in a small mountain town in Puerto
Rico Thursday, and police said the woman's husband was a suspect.
</P>
<P>
   Carmen Maldonado Santana, 26, and her children were slain in
Utuado, about 40 miles southwest of San Juan, police said. The
children ranged in age from six months to 10 years old.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they are looking for security guard Hector Mercado
Cedeno, Maldonado's husband.
</P>
<P>
   Maria Maldonado, mother and grandmother to the victims, said
that her daughter told her that she was afraid that her husband
would kill her.
</P>
<P>
   Utuado Mayor Juan Luis Ortiz said it was a shock for his
normally tranquil town.
</P>
<P>
   ''Things like this shake up everyone,'' Ortiz said.
</P>
