<DOCNO> APW20000629.0209 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 23:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Tourist Arrivals Up  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SINGAPORE (AP) -- Visitor arrivals in Singapore rose by 6.5
percent to 595,101 in May from a year earlier, the Singapore
Tourism Board said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Visitors from Africa led the growth with an increase of 28.4
percent, followed by those from Central, North and South America
with a 10.9 percent rise, the Singapore Tourism Board said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
   Visitors from Asia generated only a moderate 4.2 percent
increase.
</P>
<P>
   For the first five months of the year, 3.1 million people
visited Singapore, an increase of 13.1 percent over the same period
in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Tourism is an important industry in Singapore, a small, wealthy
island republic with 3.2 million people and no natural resources.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-29-00 2346 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000629.0210 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 23:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Workers Stop Working on Stadium  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- About 100 employees stopped work on the
controversial Olympic beach volleyball venue Friday morning after
high winds sent unsecured timber and metal flying around the work
site.
</P>
<P>
   Andrew Ferguson, state secretary of the Construction, Forestry,
Mining and Energy Union (CFMEU), said workers would be back
Saturday after a six-man safety crew gave the all-clear.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier Friday, metal frames with timber platforms making up the
slat seating went flying after wind gusts blew.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're very lucky someone hasn't been killed -- there was a
great potential for a loss of life as there's all sorts of people
who use the beach, not to mention passing traffic,'' Ferguson said.
</P>
<P>
   Olympic Coordination Authority spokesman Bob Bowden said the
problem would not affect the stadium being finished on time.
</P>
<P>
   ''The slat seating was caught up in the wind, but it hasn't
caused any damage,'' Bowden said.
</P>
<P>
   The 10,000-seat beach volleyball site is the only Sydney 2000
venue yet to be completed.
</P>
<P>
   The start of its construction in May was delayed by protesters
campaigning against the temporary stadium being built along the
city's famous tourist strip.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-29-00 2358 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000629.0211 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 23:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rocker Back in New York  </HEADLINE>
By LARRY McSHANE
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- New York Mets fan Mike Adler had waited since
last October to ask -- actually scream -- a question for John Rocker.
So when Atlanta's loudmouth lefty went out to run windsprints
Thursday night, Adler was ready.
</P>
<P>
   ''Why don't you show us respect?'' shouted Adler, proudly
